What This License Covers
-------------------------

This MIT License applies ONLY to the automation scripts, documentation, and 
configuration files in this repository, specifically:

  - Makefile and build automation
  - Shell scripts (scripts/*.sh)
  - Helm chart templates (helm/templates/*.yaml)
  - Helm values configuration (helm/values.yaml)
  - Documentation files (*.md, docs/*.md)
  - Platform engineering patterns and implementations

You are free to use, modify, and distribute these automation components under
the MIT License terms above.

What This License Does NOT Cover
----------------------------------

The following software and services require separate licenses and terms of
service acceptance. This repository does NOT grant any rights to use:

1. NVIDIA NIM Software
   - NVIDIA NIM containers and inference microservices
   - Requires: NVIDIA NIM End User License Agreement (EULA)
   - License: https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/data-center/products/nim/eula/
   - Access: Requires NGC account and API key
   - Terms: https://ngc.nvidia.com/legal/terms

2. Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI)
   - Oracle Container Engine for Kubernetes (OKE)
   - OCI compute, networking, and storage services
   - Requires: OCI account and acceptance of cloud services terms
   - Terms: https://www.oracle.com/corporate/contracts/cloud-services/
   - Billing: Pay-as-you-go based on usage

3. Meta Llama Models
   - Meta Llama 3.1 8B Instruct and other Llama models
   - Requires: Acceptance of Meta Llama license terms
   - License: https://llama.meta.com/llama3_1/license/
   - Usage: Subject to Meta's acceptable use policy

Requirements to Use This Platform
-----------------------------------

To deploy and use Nimble OKE, you MUST:

1. Obtain NVIDIA NGC account and API key (free registration)
2. Create Oracle Cloud account and accept OCI terms (paid service)
3. Review and comply with Meta Llama license terms
4. Ensure all usage complies with respective vendor terms of service
5. Understand that cloud usage incurs costs (~$12 for 5-hour smoke test)

You are responsible for:
  - Obtaining all necessary licenses and approvals
  - Complying with all vendor terms of service
  - Paying for cloud infrastructure usage
  - Ensuring lawful use of AI models
  - Meeting any regulatory requirements in your jurisdiction

Attribution and Upstream Projects
